[ MEN SHOUTING ]

01:13.240 --> 01:16.869
OH, MY GOD! NO!

01:13.240 --> 01:16.869
NO! SOMEBODY CALL FOR HELP!

01:16.911 --> 01:18.746
CALL MY LAWYER.

01:18.787 --> 01:21.081
[ ALARM CONTINUES ]

01:24.209 --> 01:26.420
GO ON, MR. ROLLINS.

01:26.461 --> 01:28.422
I...

01:28.463 --> 01:31.884
WELL, I LOST 12 BROTHERS

01:28.463 --> 01:31.884
THAT DAY.

01:31.926 --> 01:34.428
WHAT CAUSED THE EXPLOSION?

01:34.469 --> 01:36.597
IT WAS A-A BUILDUP

01:34.469 --> 01:36.597
OF METHANE GAS.

01:36.638 --> 01:39.600
SEE, THE MINE HAD

01:36.638 --> 01:39.600
SUBSTANDARD VENTILATION.

01:39.641 --> 01:41.018
I MEAN, WE ALL KNEW ABOUT IT,

01:41.060 --> 01:42.686
BUT THERE AIN'T NOTHING

01:41.060 --> 01:42.686
WE COULD DO.

01:42.728 --> 01:44.855
SO I GUESS GETTING

01:42.728 --> 01:44.855
ANOTHER LINE OF WORK

01:44.897 --> 01:46.481
WOULDN'T BE AN OPTION, HUH?

01:46.523 --> 01:48.149
MINES ARE THE ONLY WAY TO MAKE

01:46.523 --> 01:48.149
A DECENT LIVING AROUND THERE.

01:48.191 --> 01:51.152
I MEAN, I-I'M NOT LOOKING

01:48.191 --> 01:51.152
FOR YOUR CHARITY, MR. FORD.

01:51.194 --> 01:52.613
WE LIKE THE WORK.

01:52.654 --> 01:55.282
WE'D JUST LIKE TO BE ABLE

01:52.654 --> 01:55.282
TO DO IT SAFELY IS ALL.

01:55.323 --> 01:56.909
I UNDERSTAND.

01:56.951 --> 01:59.870
SO THE C.E.O. OF THE MINE,

01:56.951 --> 01:59.870
THIS DAN BLACKWELL,

01:59.912 --> 02:03.206
UH, HE RECEIVED GOVERNMENT MONEY

01:59.912 --> 02:03.206
AFTER THE EXPLOSION.

02:03.248 --> 02:04.750
FIGURES -- YOU KILL A DOZEN

02:03.248 --> 02:04.750
OF YOUR OWN MEN,

02:04.792 --> 02:06.627
AND UNCLE SAM

02:04.792 --> 02:06.627
WRITES YOU A CHECK.

02:06.668 --> 02:09.713
YEAH, THAT MONEY WAS SUPPOSED TO

02:06.668 --> 02:09.713
GO TO MINE-SAFETY IMPROVEMENTS.

02:09.755 --> 02:11.339
I DON'T KNOW

02:09.755 --> 02:11.339
WHERE THAT MONEY WENT,

02:11.381 --> 02:12.967
BUT I  CAN  TELL YOU IT DIDN'T

02:11.381 --> 02:12.967
MAKE IT INTO THE MINE.

02:13.008 --> 02:16.428
THAT PLACE IS JUST AS BAD NOW

02:13.008 --> 02:16.428
AS IT WAS TWO YEARS AGO.

02:16.470 --> 02:17.471
MAYBE WORSE.

02:17.512 --> 02:18.639
ALL RIGHT.

02:18.680 --> 02:20.599
WELL, WE'RE GONNA FIND

02:18.680 --> 02:20.599
THAT MONEY,

02:20.641 --> 02:22.977
AND WE'RE GONNA PUT IT

02:20.641 --> 02:22.977
BACK WHERE IT BELONGS.

02:23.018 --> 02:25.646
THANK YOU.

02:25.687 --> 02:27.481
THANK YOU.

02:27.522 --> 02:30.317
THE RICH AND POWERFUL

02:27.522 --> 02:30.317
TAKE WHAT THEY WANT.

02:30.358 --> 02:32.360
WE STEAL IT BACK FOR YOU.

02:39.159 --> 02:43.288
SOMETIMES, BAD GUYS

02:39.159 --> 02:43.288
MAKE THE BEST GOOD GUYS.

02:44.957 --> 02:46.249
WE PROVIDE...

02:47.501 --> 02:48.877
WELL, IT TURNS OUT

02:48.919 --> 02:51.130
BLACKWELL DID USE THE MONEY

02:48.919 --> 02:51.130
FOR SAFETY MEASURES --

02:51.170 --> 02:53.381
OR  ONE  BIG SAFETY MEASURE.

02:53.423 --> 02:55.050
SHE'S NAMED DEBRA PIERCE.

02:55.092 --> 02:57.094
WEST VIRGINIA ATTORNEY GENERAL.

02:57.136 --> 02:58.887
HER HAIR'S SO POOFY.

02:58.929 --> 03:01.765
UM, THANKS TO A RECENT

02:58.929 --> 03:01.765
SUPREME COURT DECISION

03:01.807 --> 03:04.977
REMOVING LIMITS ON CORPORATE

03:01.807 --> 03:04.977
CAMPAIGN CONTRIBUTIONS,

03:05.019 --> 03:07.646
BLACKWELL WAS ABLE TO SINK

03:05.019 --> 03:07.646
ALL OF HIS SAFETY MONEY

03:07.688 --> 03:09.272
INTO PIERCE'S

03:07.688 --> 03:09.272
POLITICAL ACTION COMMITTEE.

03:09.314 --> 03:10.858
SO INSTEAD OF MAKING

03:09.314 --> 03:10.858
THE MINES SAFER,

03:10.899 --> 03:13.110
HE JUST HIRED HIMSELF

03:10.899 --> 03:13.110
AN ATTORNEY GENERAL.

03:13.152 --> 03:15.278
YEAH. WELL, HE'S GETTING

03:13.152 --> 03:15.278
HIS MONEY'S WORTH.

03:15.320 --> 03:16.613
SINCE THE EXPLOSION

03:15.320 --> 03:16.613
TWO YEARS AGO,

03:16.655 --> 03:18.657
BLACKWELL HAS RECEIVED

03:16.655 --> 03:18.657
NEARLY 400 CITATIONS

03:18.699 --> 03:20.659
FOR UNSAFE WORKING CONDITIONS.

03:20.701 --> 03:23.787
WELL, EVEN  HE  CAN'T JUST MAKE

03:20.701 --> 03:23.787
400 CITATIONS DISAPPEAR.

03:23.829 --> 03:24.830
CAN HE?

03:24.872 --> 03:26.331
NO. BUT HE CAN BURY 'EM.

03:26.373 --> 03:28.167
WHAT HE DOES IS HE APPEALS THEM,

03:28.207 --> 03:30.502
AND PIERCE MAKES SURE THAT

03:28.207 --> 03:30.502
THOSE APPEALS GO ON FOREVER.

03:30.544 --> 03:32.880
SO WHILE THE CITATIONS

03:30.544 --> 03:32.880
ARE UNDER APPEAL,

03:32.921 --> 03:34.673
HE DOESN'T HAVE TO PAY A CENT.

03:34.715 --> 03:36.424
WE CAN'T GO AFTER BLACKWELL

03:36.466 --> 03:38.177
WITH AN A.G. IN HIS BACK POCKET.

03:38.218 --> 03:40.512
NO, BUT WE CAN TAKE DOWN

03:38.218 --> 03:40.512
BOTH OF THEM.

03:40.554 --> 03:42.305
WHAT WE DO IS WE GET BLACKWELL

03:40.554 --> 03:42.305
TO GIVE US THE MONEY

03:42.347 --> 03:43.724
FROM THE PAC,

03:43.765 --> 03:45.475
AND THEN ONCE THAT MONEY

03:43.765 --> 03:45.475
IS TRANSFERRED,

03:45.517 --> 03:49.479
WE FLAG BOTH OF THEM FOR MISUSE

03:45.517 --> 03:49.479
OF CAMPAIGN FUNDS.

03:49.521 --> 03:50.898
THE SKAGWAY SHUFFLE.

03:50.939 --> 03:52.691
YEAH.

03:50.939 --> 03:52.691
THAT'S WHAT I WAS THINKING.

03:52.733 --> 03:54.568
SEE, NOW Y'ALL ARE JUST

03:52.733 --> 03:54.568
MAKING STUFF UP.

03:54.609 --> 03:55.944
IT'S LIKE THE FIDDLE GAME.

03:55.986 --> 03:57.487
YEAH, ONLY UNDERGROUND.

03:57.529 --> 03:59.073
IS ELIOT GONNA BE

03:57.529 --> 03:59.073
THE FIDDLE AGAIN?

03:59.114 --> 04:01.075
-NO.

03:59.114 --> 04:01.075
-CAN  I  BE THE FIDDLE?

04:01.116 --> 04:02.367
-NO.

04:02.409 --> 04:03.994
THE MINE IS THE FIDDLE.

04:04.036 --> 04:05.662
WE CONVINCE HIM THAT HE'S GOT

04:04.036 --> 04:05.662
SOMETHING VALUABLE IN HIS MINE,

04:05.704 --> 04:08.248
THEN WE SELL HIM

04:05.704 --> 04:08.248
A PROCESS TO MINE IT,

04:08.289 --> 04:09.917
AND THEN WE TAKE ALL HIS MONEY.

04:09.958 --> 04:12.086
RIGHT. GOOD.

04:12.127 --> 04:14.504
SO, HOW ARE WE GONNA DO THAT?

04:14.546 --> 04:16.339
WE'RE GONNA SELL THE GUY

04:14.546 --> 04:16.339
HIS OWN MINE.

04:21.720 --> 04:23.097
ALL RIGHT. THERE HE IS.

04:23.138 --> 04:25.557
-THIS HERE IS SECTION "B."

04:23.138 --> 04:25.557
-SECTION "B." ALL RIGHT.

04:25.599 --> 04:28.102
BASICALLY, I JUST NEED YOU

04:25.599 --> 04:28.102
TO POINT ME OUT A DIRECTION

04:28.143 --> 04:29.770
WHERE I CAN BE OUT OF THE WAY.

04:29.811 --> 04:31.980
-WELL, THAT'S NO PROBLEM.

04:29.811 --> 04:31.980
THAT'D BE SECTION "C."

04:29.811 --> 04:31.980
-SECTION "C."

04:32.022 --> 04:34.566
HEY, CORY! COME HERE!

04:34.608 --> 04:36.693
HE'S A GOOD KID.

04:34.608 --> 04:36.693
HE'LL SHOW YOU AROUND.

04:36.735 --> 04:38.737
LISTEN. BE CAREFUL BACK THERE.

04:38.779 --> 04:40.739
THAT SECTION'S BEEN ABANDONED

04:38.779 --> 04:40.739
FOR YEARS,

04:40.781 --> 04:42.908
AND THEM OLD WOODEN

04:40.781 --> 04:42.908
MINE SUPPORTS IS UNSTABLE.

04:42.950 --> 04:43.909
YEAH, BOSS.

04:43.951 --> 04:44.993
THIS HERE IS ERIC.

04:45.035 --> 04:46.245
I NEED YOU TO SHOW HIM

04:45.035 --> 04:46.245
TO SECTION "C"

04:46.286 --> 04:47.621
SO HE CAN DO SOME DUST READINGS.

04:47.662 --> 04:49.748
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

04:49.790 --> 04:51.083
THIS WAY.

04:55.295 --> 04:56.463
[ American accent ] MORNING.

04:56.504 --> 04:57.547
CAN I HELP YOU?

04:57.589 --> 04:59.424
I'M CARA HETZEL.

04:57.589 --> 04:59.424
THIS IS JESSE OAKS.

04:59.466 --> 05:01.635
WE'RE HERE FROM

04:59.466 --> 05:01.635
THE MINE SAFETY COALITION

05:01.676 --> 05:02.719
TO DO A SPOT INSPECTION.

05:02.761 --> 05:04.596
FINE. LET ME GET

05:02.761 --> 05:04.596
MY MINE SUPERVISOR,

05:04.638 --> 05:06.556
SHOW YOU AROUND -- CLARK!

05:06.598 --> 05:10.477
CAN YOU, UH, BE SO KIND

05:10.518 --> 05:12.062
AS TO SHOW

05:10.518 --> 05:12.062
THE INSPECTORS AROUND?

05:12.104 --> 05:14.940
UH, BE CAREFUL WHAT KIND OF

05:12.104 --> 05:14.940
ROCKS YOU TURN OVER DOWN THERE.

05:14.982 --> 05:16.858
MINING CAN BE

05:14.982 --> 05:16.858
A DANGEROUS BUSINESS.

05:16.900 --> 05:18.318
IT SURE CAN.

05:21.822 --> 05:24.032
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

05:26.493 --> 05:27.953
WHO ARE  YOU?

05:27.995 --> 05:29.621
UH, HEY, UH, MR. BLACKWELL.

05:27.995 --> 05:29.621
BOB GIBSON.

05:29.663 --> 05:31.832
I'M HERE TO MAKE YOU AN OFFER

05:29.663 --> 05:31.832
YOU CAN'T REFUSE.

05:31.873 --> 05:33.959
-[ Chuckling ] REALLY?

05:31.873 --> 05:33.959
-I WANT TO BUY YOUR MINE.

05:34.001 --> 05:35.460
EXCUSE ME?

05:35.502 --> 05:37.587
OH, SORRY. I DIDN'T REALIZE

05:35.502 --> 05:37.587
YOU WERE HARD OF HEARING.

05:37.629 --> 05:39.131
I HEARD THAT CAN HAPPEN

05:37.629 --> 05:39.131
TO  MINERS.

05:39.173 --> 05:41.800
[ Loud voice ]

05:39.173 --> 05:41.800
I WANT TO BUY YOUR MINE.

05:41.842 --> 05:43.468
MINE'S NOT FOR SALE.

05:43.510 --> 05:45.012
[ Chuckling ]

05:43.510 --> 05:45.012
I WAS AFRAID YOU'D SAY THAT.

05:45.053 --> 05:46.596
SO, ALL RIGHT, I'M GONNA WRITE

05:45.053 --> 05:46.596
DOWN A LITTLE NUMBER HERE,

05:46.638 --> 05:48.765
AND WE'LL STOP PLAYING

05:46.638 --> 05:48.765
THESE GAMES.

05:48.807 --> 05:50.642
THE MINE IS  NOT  FOR  SALE.

05:50.684 --> 05:52.019
OR ARE  YOU  HARD OF HEARING?

05:52.060 --> 05:53.812
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE RUDE.

05:53.854 --> 05:55.522
I JUST WANT TO GIVE YOU

05:53.854 --> 05:55.522
AN OPPORTUNITY

05:55.563 --> 05:56.648
TO MAKE A LOT OF MONEY.

05:56.690 --> 05:58.233
NOW, LOOK,

05:56.690 --> 05:58.233
I KNOW YOU COUNTRY FOLK,

05:58.275 --> 05:59.358
YOU LIKE THE SIMPLE LIFE.

05:59.400 --> 06:01.653
BUT THE SIMPLE LIFE

05:59.400 --> 06:01.653
LOOKS A LOT BETTER

06:01.695 --> 06:03.697
ON THE BACK

06:01.695 --> 06:03.697
OF A 100-FOOT YACHT, SAY.

06:03.738 --> 06:06.200
I APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY,

06:03.738 --> 06:06.200
MR. GILMAN.

06:06.241 --> 06:07.492
GIBSON. BOB GIBSON.

06:07.534 --> 06:08.827
GIBSON. YEAH.

06:08.869 --> 06:11.370
WELL, I'M DOING FINE ON MY OWN.

06:11.412 --> 06:12.831
[ LAUGHS ]

06:12.873 --> 06:13.999
OKAY.

06:14.041 --> 06:15.209
IF YOU SAY SO.

06:15.250 --> 06:17.002
LISTEN, IF YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND,

06:17.044 --> 06:18.920
GIVE ME A CALL.

06:22.924 --> 06:24.968
OKAY, PARKER.

06:22.924 --> 06:24.968
ARE YOU IN PLACE?

06:26.928 --> 06:28.638
UH, ALMOST.

06:28.680 --> 06:31.016
YOU SURE SOMEONE ELSE

06:28.680 --> 06:31.016
CAN'T DO THIS?

06:31.058 --> 06:32.684
UH, WELL, WE NEED ALL HANDS

06:31.058 --> 06:32.684
ON DECK ON THIS ONE.

06:32.726 --> 06:34.895
Just do what Sophie told you.

06:34.936 --> 06:38.106
A GREAT GRIFT IS LIKE A ROMANCE.

06:38.148 --> 06:41.026
YOU HAVE TO FIND OUT

06:38.148 --> 06:41.026
WHAT THEY WANT

06:41.068 --> 06:43.195
AND JUST GIVE IT TO THEM.

06:43.237 --> 06:44.612
YOU HAVE TO WOO THEM.

06:44.654 --> 06:46.073
I DON'T WOO.

06:47.366 --> 06:49.701
TELL ME HOW YOU BREAK

06:47.366 --> 06:49.701
INTO A BANK.

06:49.743 --> 06:51.536
CLOCK THE CAMERAS,

06:49.743 --> 06:51.536
COUNT THE GUARDS,

06:51.578 --> 06:54.039
FIND THE SILENT ALARMS,

06:51.578 --> 06:54.039
LOOK FOR A WEAK SPOT TO ENTER,

06:54.081 --> 06:56.415
PICK THE VAULT'S COMBINATION,

06:54.081 --> 06:56.415
AND STEAL THE MONEY.

06:56.457 --> 07:00.045
JUST ANALYZE PIERCE THE SAME WAY

06:56.457 --> 07:00.045
YOU WOULD A SECURITY SYSTEM.

07:00.087 --> 07:02.630
HERE. TAKE NOTES.

07:04.132 --> 07:06.176
THERE'S YOUR MARK.

07:06.218 --> 07:08.220
FIND  HER  WEAK SPOTS.

07:08.262 --> 07:11.223
WITH POLITICIANS, IT'S USUALLY

07:08.262 --> 07:11.223
A NEED FOR ADORATION.

07:11.265 --> 07:12.807
THE SAME WAY THAT YOU WEAR BLACK

07:12.849 --> 07:14.684
TO MASK YOURSELF

07:12.849 --> 07:14.684
FROM SECURITY CAMERAS,

07:14.726 --> 07:16.895
FLATTERY CAN MASK

07:14.726 --> 07:16.895
YOUR INTENTIONS.

07:16.937 --> 07:18.772
FIND THE RIGHT COMBINATION,

07:18.813 --> 07:21.524
AND YOU CAN UNLOCK

07:18.813 --> 07:21.524
THE MARK'S TRUST.

07:21.566 --> 07:23.818
AND THEN YOU CAN STEAL HER...

07:23.860 --> 07:25.279
...SOUL.

07:26.321 --> 07:28.949
I WAS GONNA SAY "CONFIDENCE."

07:31.118 --> 07:34.829
YOU CAN DO THIS, PARKER.

07:31.118 --> 07:34.829
JUST TRUST YOUR INSTINCTS.

07:38.750 --> 07:40.085
PARKER, GO!

07:40.127 --> 07:41.461
OKAY.

07:40.127 --> 07:41.461
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

07:41.502 --> 07:43.338
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

07:44.839 --> 07:47.175
UNDER MY CONTINUED DIRECTION,

07:47.217 --> 07:48.969
THE PEOPLE OF WEST VIRGINIA

07:49.010 --> 07:52.097
WILL BE KNOWN AS THE PEOPLE

07:49.010 --> 07:52.097
WHO LOVE FREEDOM,

07:52.139 --> 07:53.348
WHO LOVE JUSTICE,

07:53.390 --> 07:55.767
AND WHO FIGHT

07:53.390 --> 07:55.767
FOR WHAT THEY LOVE!

07:55.809 --> 08:00.063
AND...AND WHO  FIGHT

07:55.809 --> 08:00.063
FOR WHAT THEY LOVE.

08:00.105 --> 08:02.983
WILL YOU LET ME CONTINUE

08:00.105 --> 08:02.983
TO FIGHT FOR YOU?

08:03.024 --> 08:04.859
YES, YES, AND YES!

08:04.901 --> 08:06.611
[ LAUGHS, CLAPS ]

08:06.653 --> 08:07.821
BEAUTIFUL SPEECH, MS. PIERCE.

08:07.862 --> 08:09.823
-WHO ARE YOU?

08:07.862 --> 08:09.823
-I'M YOUR BIGGEST FAN...

08:09.864 --> 08:11.992
AND HOPEFULLY,

08:09.864 --> 08:11.992
YOUR NEW CAMPAIGN CONSULTANT.

08:12.033 --> 08:13.952
-[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

08:12.033 --> 08:13.952
-I'VE BEEN FOLLOWING YOUR CAREER

08:13.994 --> 08:15.495
SINCE YOUR FIRST TERM

08:13.994 --> 08:15.495
IN THE STATE SENATE.

08:15.536 --> 08:17.956
AND THIS IS YOUR CHAMBER

08:17.998 --> 08:20.792
WHERE YOU DISPENSE JUSTICE

08:17.998 --> 08:20.792
AND FIGHT FOR FREEDOM!

08:20.834 --> 08:22.294
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

08:22.336 --> 08:23.962
STILL DIDN'T CATCH YOUR NAME,

08:22.336 --> 08:23.962
SWEETIE.

08:24.004 --> 08:26.131
OH, KELLY BETH?

08:24.004 --> 08:26.131
KELLY BETH LAUGHLIN?

08:26.173 --> 08:28.091
BUT YOU CAN CALL ME KELLY BETH.

08:28.133 --> 08:29.884
CAN I CALL YOU "BOSS"?

08:29.926 --> 08:32.095
[ Chuckling ] OH, DARLIN',

08:29.926 --> 08:32.095
AS MUCH AS I'D LOVE YOUR ENERGY

08:32.137 --> 08:34.181
IN THE HOMESTRETCH

08:32.137 --> 08:34.181
OF THIS CAMPAIGN,

08:34.222 --> 08:36.433
I DON'T HAVE MUCH OF A BUDGET

08:34.222 --> 08:36.433
FOR A CAMPAIGN CONSULTANT.

08:36.475 --> 08:38.185
I'M KELLY BETH LAUGHLIN...

08:38.226 --> 08:40.312
[ BEEP ]

08:40.354 --> 08:41.980
...OF THE MAYSVILLE LAUGHLINS.

08:42.022 --> 08:43.648
SEE, I DON'T NEED

08:42.022 --> 08:43.648
A SALARY, OKAY?

08:43.690 --> 08:45.317
IN FACT, I WOULD PAY

08:43.690 --> 08:45.317
FOR THE EXPERIENCE

08:45.359 --> 08:46.651
OF WORKING FOR YOU.

08:46.693 --> 08:48.945
WELL, DAMN, I'M HAPPY TO WORK

08:46.693 --> 08:48.945
WITH ANYBODY

08:48.987 --> 08:50.280
WILLING TO PAY FOR IT.

08:50.322 --> 08:51.323
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:51.365 --> 08:52.991
