TO KEEP A BUSINESS

19:05.478 --> 19:07.647
AND MAKE A BUCK.

19:07.688 --> 19:09.482
MM-HMM.

19:09.523 --> 19:11.985
I'M PRETTY CONFIDENT,

19:09.523 --> 19:11.985
USING THIS PROCESS,

19:12.026 --> 19:14.528
YOU'LL BE ABLE TO MAKE

19:12.026 --> 19:14.528
QUITE A FEW  BUCKS.

19:14.570 --> 19:16.322
WELL, I'M CONVINCED.

19:16.363 --> 19:17.991
EXCELLENT.

19:18.032 --> 19:19.826
LET'S TALK NUMBERS.

19:19.867 --> 19:23.537
ALL RIGHT. WELL,

19:19.867 --> 19:23.537
HE'S GOT $125,000 LIQUID...

19:23.579 --> 19:27.083
AND $500,000 IN THE PAC.

19:27.125 --> 19:28.668
$600,000.

19:28.709 --> 19:30.461
WE'RE GONNA NEED IT

19:28.709 --> 19:30.461
IN ONE PAYMENT.

19:30.503 --> 19:33.006
WE'VE FOUND THAT INSTALLMENTS

19:30.503 --> 19:33.006
CAN GET A LITTLE BIT MESSY.

19:33.047 --> 19:34.007
OF COURSE.

19:34.048 --> 19:35.466
BY TOMORROW.

19:35.508 --> 19:37.343
MR. GIBSON WAS GONNA WRITE US

19:35.508 --> 19:37.343
A CHECK IN THE MORNING.

19:37.384 --> 19:39.261
NOW, IF THAT'S GONNA BE

19:37.384 --> 19:39.261
A PROBLEM FOR YOU...

19:39.303 --> 19:41.014
NO. THAT'S...NO PROBLEM.

19:41.055 --> 19:42.515
I'M HAVING A FUNDRAISER

19:42.556 --> 19:44.600
FOR THE ATTORNEY GENERAL

19:42.556 --> 19:44.600
AT THE MORGAN CLUB TOMORROW.

19:44.642 --> 19:46.769
YOU STOP BY THERE,

19:44.642 --> 19:46.769
I'LL CUT YOU A CHECK.

19:46.811 --> 19:48.270
PERFECT.

19:48.312 --> 19:50.606
OKAY, ELIOT.

19:48.312 --> 19:50.606
SOPHIE'S DONE WITH BLACKWELL.

19:50.648 --> 19:51.691
HE'S HOOKED.

19:51.732 --> 19:53.151
You can surface.

19:53.192 --> 19:56.236
AHH. I DON'T WANT TO LEAVE

19:53.192 --> 19:56.236
THESE GUYS ONE MAN DOWN.

19:56.278 --> 19:57.446
Okay. Fine.

19:56.278 --> 19:57.446
You can finish the day.

19:57.488 --> 19:59.406
But tomorrow, we're gone.

19:59.448 --> 20:01.534
PAUL REVERE MAKE THAT LUNCHBOX?

20:01.575 --> 20:02.952
[ LAUGHS ]

20:02.994 --> 20:04.662
NOPE.

20:04.704 --> 20:06.246
THIS WAS MADE IN 1958.

20:06.288 --> 20:08.415
PAUL REVERE DIED

20:06.288 --> 20:08.415
IN THE EARLY 1800s.

20:08.457 --> 20:10.126
WHAT?

20:10.168 --> 20:12.086
YOU DON'T THINK I KNOW

20:10.168 --> 20:12.086
WHO PAUL REVERE IS?

20:12.128 --> 20:14.380
-ALL RIGHT, SMARTASS.

20:12.128 --> 20:14.380
-[ CHUCKLES ]

20:15.422 --> 20:16.883
THIS WAS MY DAD'S.

20:16.924 --> 20:19.635
GRANDPA'S BEFORE THAT.

20:21.762 --> 20:23.931
HEY. SCOOP SEEMS TO BE RUNNING

20:21.762 --> 20:23.931
A LITTLE SLOW THIS MORNING.

20:23.973 --> 20:25.892
TRANSMISSION'S SLIPPING AGAIN.

20:25.933 --> 20:28.310
ALL RIGHT.

20:25.933 --> 20:28.310
WELL, I'LL LOOK INTO IT.

20:30.063 --> 20:32.899
YOU KNOW, YOU WANT TO BE THE MAN

20:30.063 --> 20:32.899
OF THE HOUSE...

20:32.940 --> 20:34.233
THAT'S THE WAY RIGHT THERE.

20:34.274 --> 20:36.069
FUTURE'S IN THE MACHINES.

20:36.110 --> 20:37.904
IT'S FASTER, IT'S SAFER.

20:37.945 --> 20:39.488
YOU WANT TO PROVIDE

20:37.945 --> 20:39.488
FOR YOUR FAMILY,

20:39.530 --> 20:41.741
LEARN HOW TO USE THE SCOOP.

20:41.782 --> 20:43.283
I'M JUST SAYING.

20:43.325 --> 20:45.411
YOU GOT A GOOD HEAD FOR IT...

20:45.452 --> 20:46.453
PAUL REVERE.

20:46.495 --> 20:48.915
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:48.956 --> 20:51.584
OOH, YOUR LATEST NUMBERS ARE UP.

20:51.625 --> 20:53.211
OOH.

20:53.252 --> 20:55.755
SIGNIFICANTLY  UP.

20:55.796 --> 20:58.216
I DON'T THINK I EVER SEEN IT

20:55.796 --> 20:58.216
JUMP  THIS  HIGH.

20:58.257 --> 20:59.550
REALLY?

20:59.592 --> 21:01.468
HEY.

20:59.592 --> 21:01.468
NATE SAID TO MAKE THEM HIGHER.

21:01.510 --> 21:04.597
HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO KNOW

21:01.510 --> 21:04.597
WHAT'S "SIGNIFICANTLY HIGHER"

21:04.638 --> 21:06.182
and what's

21:04.638 --> 21:06.182
"insignificantly higher"?

21:06.224 --> 21:07.600
NO, THAT'S FINE.

21:07.641 --> 21:09.852
W-WE JUST NEED HER TO FEEL

21:07.641 --> 21:09.852
SHE HAS A COMFORTABLE LEAD

21:09.894 --> 21:12.146
SO SHE'LL BE FINE WITH BLACKWELL

21:09.894 --> 21:12.146
USING THE PAC FUNDS.

21:12.188 --> 21:15.274
WELL, WE MUST BE

21:12.188 --> 21:15.274
DOING  SOMETHING  RIGHT.

21:15.315 --> 21:18.027
YEAH, MUST BE

21:15.315 --> 21:18.027
YOUR LATEST COMMERCIAL...

21:18.069 --> 21:20.738
OR YOUR HAIR --

21:18.069 --> 21:20.738
PEOPLE  LOVE  YOUR HAIR.

21:20.780 --> 21:21.781
-REALLY?

21:20.780 --> 21:21.781
-YEAH.

21:21.822 --> 21:22.990
[ DOOR OPENS ]

21:24.909 --> 21:26.452
HELLO, DAN.

21:29.580 --> 21:31.791
REFILL? OKAY.

21:31.832 --> 21:33.793
I LIKE THIS ONE.

21:35.669 --> 21:39.339
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

21:39.381 --> 21:42.135
BLACKWELL'S HERE.

21:39.381 --> 21:42.135
IT'S HAPPENING.

21:42.176 --> 21:43.719
NO!

21:43.761 --> 21:44.720
NO WAY!

21:44.762 --> 21:46.346
I HAVE AN ELECTION COMING UP.

21:46.388 --> 21:48.015
THE COLTAN MINE'S

21:46.388 --> 21:48.015
NOT GONNA DO YOU ANY GOOD

21:48.057 --> 21:50.017
WITHOUT  ME  IN OFFICE KEEPING IT

21:48.057 --> 21:50.017
FROM GETTING SHUT DOWN!

21:50.059 --> 21:52.228
IF I DON'T HAVE THAT MONEY

21:50.059 --> 21:52.228
BY TOMORROW,

21:52.270 --> 21:53.980
THEY'RE GONNA SELL THIS PROCESS

21:52.270 --> 21:53.980
TO GIBSON.

21:54.021 --> 21:56.232
SO? USE THE MINE'S MONEY.

21:56.274 --> 21:59.318
The mine doesn't have

21:56.274 --> 21:59.318
that sort of liquidity.

21:59.359 --> 22:01.028
You're paying your workers

21:59.359 --> 22:01.028
with something, aren't you?

22:01.070 --> 22:04.364
YEAH. I-I SUPPOSE

22:01.070 --> 22:04.364
I COULD TAKE THE...

22:04.406 --> 22:05.532
MONEY OUT THE PAYROLL.

22:05.574 --> 22:07.534
BUT THAT WOULD BANKRUPT

22:05.574 --> 22:07.534
THE MINE.

22:07.576 --> 22:10.037
YOU SAY THAT

22:07.576 --> 22:10.037
LIKE IT'S A  BAD  THING.

22:16.919 --> 22:18.045
ALL RIGHT.

22:18.087 --> 22:19.505
HERE WE GO.

22:19.546 --> 22:21.340
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

22:21.381 --> 22:22.758
CLARK?

22:22.800 --> 22:25.845
TELL THE MEN NOT TO COME

22:22.800 --> 22:25.845
TO WORK TOMORROW.

22:25.886 --> 22:27.263
ALL OF 'EM.

22:27.305 --> 22:30.141
AND MAKE SURE THERE'S NOBODY

22:27.305 --> 22:30.141
IN THAT MINE.

22:30.183 --> 22:31.517
AND THEN CALL ME BACK.

22:31.558 --> 22:34.687
I GOT A JOB OF WORK

22:31.558 --> 22:34.687
FOR YOU TO DO.

22:34.728 --> 22:37.315
WELL, THAT'S A GREAT DAY'S WORK.

22:37.397 --> 22:38.316
UGH.

22:38.356 --> 22:40.109
BLACKWELL'S SHUTTING DOWN

22:38.356 --> 22:40.109
THE MINE

22:40.151 --> 22:42.069
AND USING THE PAYROLL MONEY

22:40.151 --> 22:42.069
TO PAY  US.

22:42.111 --> 22:43.737
SO WE'VE JUST BANKRUPTED

22:42.111 --> 22:43.737
AN ENTIRE TOWN.

22:43.779 --> 22:44.905
Worse.

22:44.947 --> 22:47.616
HE'S NOT JUST SHUTTING DOWN

22:44.947 --> 22:47.616
THE MINE.

22:47.658 --> 22:49.035
HE'S BLOWING IT UP.

22:49.076 --> 22:50.203
UGH.

22:49.076 --> 22:50.203
THAT  DOES  SOUND WORSE.

22:50.244 --> 22:51.453
You know, working in insurance,

22:51.495 --> 22:53.539
I'VE SEEN THIS PLAY

22:51.495 --> 22:53.539
A THOUSAND TIMES.

22:53.580 --> 22:55.624
AND NOW THAT WE'VE CONVINCED HIM

22:53.580 --> 22:55.624
HE HAS COLTAN,

22:55.666 --> 22:57.710
HIS MINE IS WORTH MORE DEAD

22:55.666 --> 22:57.710
THAN ALIVE.

22:57.751 --> 22:59.586
YEAH, BUT HE'S NOT GONNA

22:57.751 --> 22:59.586
HAVE TIME TO GET A BOMB

22:59.628 --> 23:01.130
AND PLANT IT IN THE MINE

22:59.628 --> 23:01.130
BY TOMORROW.

23:01.172 --> 23:03.216
WELL, HIS MINE IS PRACTICALLY

23:01.172 --> 23:03.216
A BOMB ALREADY.

23:03.257 --> 23:04.550
I MEAN, YOU COULD THROW

23:03.257 --> 23:04.550
A LIT CIGARETTE THERE,

23:04.591 --> 23:05.885
AND THAT THING WOULD BLOW.

23:05.926 --> 23:08.179
-WON'T TAKE MUCH.

23:05.926 --> 23:08.179
-WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO, NATE?

23:08.221 --> 23:11.640
WE'RE GONNA CONVINCE HIM THAT

23:08.221 --> 23:11.640
YOU'RE A LYING, GREEDY BITCH.

23:16.645 --> 23:19.523
OKAY, I'M GONNA CALL BLACKWELL

23:16.645 --> 23:19.523
AND DRAW HIM HERE.

23:19.565 --> 23:22.360
I MEAN, HE'S NOT

23:19.565 --> 23:22.360
GONNA BLOW UP THE MINE

23:19.565 --> 23:22.360
WHILE HE'S IN IT, IS HE?

23:22.400 --> 23:25.112
-THAT WILL GIVE US

23:22.400 --> 23:25.112
ENOUGH TIME TO FIND THE BOMB.

23:22.400 --> 23:25.112
-OH, YEAH. PLENTY OF TIME.

23:25.154 --> 23:26.613
MEANWHILE, I'LL BE HERE,

23:25.154 --> 23:26.613
IN THE VAN,

23:26.655 --> 23:28.241
AS FAR AWAY FROM THE MINE

23:26.655 --> 23:28.241
AS POSSIBLE.

23:28.282 --> 23:29.491
MY DUDE. GO WITH GOD.

23:29.533 --> 23:31.618
WHAT ARE YOU DOING, MAN?

23:31.660 --> 23:33.037
FOR MORALE, MAN!

23:33.079 --> 23:35.164
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

23:33.079 --> 23:35.164
LET'S GET THIS SHOW ON THE ROAD.

23:35.206 --> 23:37.833
MR. BLACKWELL.

23:37.875 --> 23:39.793
UH, YEAH, IT'S,

23:37.875 --> 23:39.793
UH, BOB GIBSON HERE.

23:39.835 --> 23:42.088
MR. GIBSON.

23:39.835 --> 23:42.088
YOU CALLING TO CONCEDE?

23:42.129 --> 23:43.547
No, I'm calling to tell you

23:43.589 --> 23:45.049
THAT WE'VE BOTH BEEN HAD.

23:45.091 --> 23:47.385
YEAH, THERE'S NO COLTAN IN

23:45.091 --> 23:47.385
YOUR MINE OR ANYWHERE NEAR IT.

23:47.425 --> 23:49.303
AH, I SHOULD HAVE PEGGED  YOU

23:47.425 --> 23:49.303
FOR A SORE LOSER.

23:49.345 --> 23:50.888
Well, listen,

23:49.345 --> 23:50.888
I can prove it to you.

23:50.930 --> 23:52.723
JUST MEET ME AT THE MINE

23:50.930 --> 23:52.723
IN 15 MINUTES.

23:52.765 --> 23:55.559
N-- THE MINE'S

23:52.765 --> 23:55.559
NOT A GOOD IDEA.

23:55.601 --> 23:57.686
-Now, maybe we can meet

23:55.601 --> 23:57.686
somewhere el--

23:55.601 --> 23:57.686
[ BEEPS ]

23:57.728 --> 23:59.605
[ SIGHS ]

23:59.646 --> 24:02.066
[ BEEPING ]

24:02.108 --> 24:04.526
[ Ringing ]

24:04.568 --> 24:06.444
This is Clark.

24:04.568 --> 24:06.444
Leave a message.

24:06.486 --> 24:07.445
-CLARK --

24:06.486 --> 24:07.445
[ Beeps ]

24:07.487 --> 24:09.115
L-LISTEN.

24:07.487 --> 24:09.115
WHERE THE HELL ARE YOU?

24:09.156 --> 24:10.574
NOW, DON'T PLANT THE DEVICE.

24:10.616 --> 24:12.118
I'M ON MY WAY TO THE MINE NOW.

24:12.159 --> 24:15.162
DO  NOT  PLANT THE DEVICE.

24:15.204 --> 24:17.248
HE'S ON HIS WAY TO YOU NOW.

24:17.290 --> 24:19.750
ALL RIGHT.

24:17.290 --> 24:19.750
WHILE THEY DEAL WITH BLACKWELL,

24:19.792 --> 24:21.752
WE'VE GOT TO SPOOK PIERCE.

24:21.794 --> 24:22.795
ON IT.

24:22.836 --> 24:24.338
SO WE NEED GHOSTS.

24:24.380 --> 24:26.799
NO. WE NEED SECRETS.

24:26.840 --> 24:29.927
WE'VE GOT TO GET HER TO MOVE

24:26.840 --> 24:29.927
THE MONEY OUT OF THE PAC.

24:29.969 --> 24:31.387
THANK YOU.

24:31.429 --> 24:32.763
RIGHT.

24:32.805 --> 24:34.848
TELL ME  EVERYTHING

24:32.805 --> 24:34.848
YOU KNOW ABOUT HER.

24:34.890 --> 24:37.601
OKAY. I'VE GOT SOME

24:34.890 --> 24:37.601
REALLY GOOD STUFF IN HERE.

24:37.643 --> 24:39.519
OKAY, SHE LIKES SUGAR

24:37.643 --> 24:39.519
IN HER COFFEE --

24:39.561 --> 24:40.813
LOTS  OF SUGAR.

24:40.854 --> 24:42.440
AND SHE HIDES TASTY TREATS

24:40.854 --> 24:42.440
IN HER DESK.

24:42.522 --> 24:44.482
SHE'S GOT A SWEET TOOTH --

24:42.522 --> 24:44.482
MAYBE WE COULD USE THAT.

24:44.524 --> 24:45.901
PROBABLY NOT. WHAT ELSE?

24:45.943 --> 24:48.904
UM...SHE NEVER TAKES CALLS

24:45.943 --> 24:48.904
FROM HER MOTHER.

24:48.946 --> 24:50.739
NO? OOH! OOH!

24:50.781 --> 24:52.699
I GOT IT --

24:50.781 --> 24:52.699
SHE -- SHE MIXES HER BLUE PENS

24:52.741 --> 24:55.493
WITH HER BLACK PENS --

24:52.741 --> 24:55.493
IN THE SAME CUP.

24:55.535 --> 24:57.079
LIKE...

24:55.535 --> 24:57.079
MIXES THEM TOGETHER.

24:57.121 --> 24:58.080
YEAH.

24:58.122 --> 24:59.623
PARKER,

24:58.122 --> 24:59.623
I'M LOOKING FOR SOMETHING

24:59.665 --> 25:01.041
THAT SOMEONE MIGHT FIND WEIRD.

25:01.083 --> 25:02.751
SOMEONE NORMAL.

25:02.793 --> 25:06.130
UM, YEAH.

25:02.793 --> 25:06.130
SOMEONE NORMAL MIGHT FIND WEIRD.

25:06.172 --> 25:09.091
MM. UH...

25:13.679 --> 25:15.055
WELL, THURSDAY AFTERNOON,

25:15.097 --> 25:17.141
SHE HAD A CLOSED-DOOR MEETING

25:15.097 --> 25:17.141
WITH BLACKWELL,

25:17.183 --> 25:19.059
BUT...IT SOUNDED LIKE

25:17.183 --> 25:19.059
THEY WERE WORKING OUT.

25:19.101 --> 25:22.062
-"WORKING OUT"?

25:19.101 --> 25:22.062
-MM-HMM.

25:22.104 --> 25:24.273
HARDISON, DO YOU STILL HAVE

25:22.104 --> 25:24.273
THE AUDIO FILE SAVED?

25:24.315 --> 25:26.900
YEAH. BUT THERE'S

25:24.315 --> 25:26.900
LIKE 100 HOURS OF IT.

25:26.942 --> 25:28.819
I-I HAVEN'T LISTENED

25:26.942 --> 25:28.819
TO IT ALL YET.

25:28.861 --> 25:31.322
NO. JUST PULL UP THE FILES

25:28.861 --> 25:31.322
FROM THURSDAY AFTERNOON.

25:31.364 --> 25:33.324
-BETWEEN 3:26 AND 4:15.

25:31.364 --> 25:33.324
-Okay. One second.

25:33.366 --> 25:34.783
[ BEEPING ]

25:34.825 --> 25:37.661
YEAH! YEAH! YEAH!

25:37.703 --> 25:39.205
-[  MOANING  ]

25:37.703 --> 25:39.205
-NO!

25:39.246 --> 25:41.457
NO! EW! OLD PEOPLE! EW!

25:41.499 --> 25:43.750
[  Moaning continues  ]

25:43.792 --> 25:45.585
PARKER, THEY'RE NOT WORKING OUT.

25:45.627 --> 25:48.088
THEY'RE...YOU KNOW.

25:49.340 --> 25:52.051
SEX, PARKER!

25:49.340 --> 25:52.051
THEY'RE KNOCKING BOOTS.

25:52.092 --> 25:54.220
OH. YEAH.

25:54.261 --> 25:55.762
CAN YOU USE THAT?

25:55.804 --> 25:58.432
WITH THAT...

25:58.474 --> 26:01.643
I CAN MAKE HER DO

25:58.474 --> 26:01.643
ANYTHING I WANT.

26:01.685 --> 26:04.562
Hey, look, y'all,

26:01.685 --> 26:04.562
this has been real cool,

26:04.604 --> 26:06.315
BUT I HAVE TO GET BACK TO,

26:04.604 --> 26:06.315
YOU KNOW,

26:06.357 --> 26:07.649
HELPING ELIOT FIND THE BOMB.

26:13.906 --> 26:16.325
I'M SWITCHING OUT OXYGEN METER.

26:19.703 --> 26:20.954
All right, man.

26:20.996 --> 26:22.622
LOOK, I'VE HACKED

26:20.996 --> 26:22.622
INTO THEIR MONITORING SYSTEM

26:22.664 --> 26:25.459
TO DETECTS PEAKS IN ANY HEAT

26:22.664 --> 26:25.459
OR METHANE LEVELS

26:25.501 --> 26:26.793
TO SHOW US WHERE CLARK

26:25.501 --> 26:26.793
PLANTED THE BOMB.

26:26.835 --> 26:28.546
-WHERE'S IT AT?

26:26.835 --> 26:28.546
-No idea.

26:28.586 --> 26:30.130
THIS THING RUNS LIKE AN ATARI.

26:30.172 --> 26:32.425
IT'S GREAT IF YOU WANT TO PLAY

26:30.172 --> 26:32.425
"FROGGER," BUT TO FIND A BOMB?

26:32.466 --> 26:33.884
While you're playing

26:32.466 --> 26:33.884
video games,

26:33.926 --> 26:35.928
I'M GONNA STILL BE LOOKING

26:33.926 --> 26:35.928
FOR THE BOMB.

26:35.969 --> 26:38.097
IF YOU DECIDE TO BE HELPFUL,

26:35.969 --> 26:38.097
LET ME KNOW.

26:41.599 --> 26:44.686
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

26:46.522 --> 26:49.442
AND THANK YOU SO MUCH

26:46.522 --> 26:49.442
FOR YOUR CONTRIBUTION.

26:49.483 --> 26:51.651
NICE TO MEET YOU.

26:49.483 --> 26:51.651
[ CHUCKLES ] YEAH.

26:51.693 --> 26:55.239
OH, MS. PIERCE, I WAS HOPING

26:51.693 --> 26:55.239
TO STEAL A MINUTE OF YOUR TIME.

26:55.281 --> 26:57.157
I'VE HEARD SO MUCH ABOUT YOU.

26:57.199 --> 26:58.284
OF COURSE, MS...

26:58.325 --> 27:00.077
OH, TINSON. ELOISE TINSON.

27:00.119 --> 27:01.870
OH, RIGHT.

27:01.912 --> 27:03.497
THE COLTAN WOMAN. HUH?

27:03.539 --> 27:04.957
IN THE FLESH.

27:04.998 --> 27:06.708
I HAVE TO SAY,

27:04.998 --> 27:06.708
IT'S BEEN SUCH A DELIGHT

27:06.750 --> 27:08.335
WORKING WITH DANNY.

27:08.377 --> 27:09.711
"DANNY"?

27:09.753 --> 27:11.297
[ Chuckling ]

27:09.753 --> 27:11.297
YOU MEAN MR. BLACKWELL.

27:11.338 --> 27:12.506
OF COURSE.

27:12.548 --> 27:14.592
YOU KNOW, THE ADDITION

27:12.548 --> 27:14.592
OF THIS COLTAN MINE

27:14.632 --> 27:16.343
IS GONNA DO WONDERS

27:14.632 --> 27:16.343
FOR THE STATE,

27:16.385 --> 27:18.554
AND I WANTED TO THANK YOU

27:16.385 --> 27:18.554
PERSONALLY

27:18.596 --> 27:20.055
FOR YOUR CONTRIBUTION.

27:20.097 --> 27:21.432
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:20.097 --> 27:21.432
I'M SORRY?

27:21.474 --> 27:22.766
MY CONTRIBUTION?

27:22.808 --> 27:24.310
WELL, THERE'S NO NEED

27:22.808 --> 27:24.310
TO BE MODEST.

27:24.351 --> 27:25.311
IT'S YOUR MONEY.

27:25.352 --> 27:26.437
OR IS IT THE PAC MONEY?

27:26.479 --> 27:28.063
I NEVER QUITE GOT THAT STRAIGHT.

27:28.105 --> 27:29.565
WELL, THAT'S ODD,

27:29.607 --> 27:31.775
BECAUSE YESTERDAY HE TOLD ME

27:29.607 --> 27:31.775
HE WAS USING THE MINE FUNDS

27:31.817 --> 27:33.068
FOR THE PURCHASE.

27:33.110 --> 27:35.154
OH, NO. THAT'S NOT

